Reasoning: The workbook has one sheet with columns A ("A List") and B ("B List") and several empty columns. The task is to count occurrences of the letter “A” in column B, and also count “A” in column A when the corresponding cell in column B is empty. The appropriate Excel formula for this is:

```
=COUNTIFS($B:$B,"A")+COUNTIFS($A:$A,"A",$B:$B,"")
```

We will place the result in a new column (C) with a header “Count”. The header will be written to C1, and the formula to C2 (the formula will evaluate the whole columns, so a single cell is sufficient). After writing, we will save the workbook to the output directory, recalculate, and verify that the formula cell is not None.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from openpyxl.utils import get_column_letter
import os

# Paths
input_path = "/sandbox/input/input_spreadsheet/1_50088_init.xlsx"
output_dir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet/"
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)
output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, "1_50088_init.xlsx")

# Load workbook (keep formulas)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]

# Write header for result column (C)
ws["C1"] = "Count"

# Write the counting formula in C2
ws["C2"] = '=COUNTIFS($B:$B,"A")+COUNTIFS($A:$A,"A",$B:$B,"")'

# Save workbook
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate formulas (LibreOffice)
recalculate(output_path)

# Verify the formula cell after recalculation
wb_check = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_check = wb_check[wb_check.sheetnames[0]]
result_val = ws_check["C2"].value
print("Result in C2 after recalculation:", result_val)
```
